Turkish Equity Movers: Aksigorta, Asya, Borusan, Celebi Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-10T16:30:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/turkish-equity-movers-aksigorta-asya-borusan-celebi-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  gained 685.39, or 1.1 percent, to 63,5169.22 at the 5:30
p.m. close of trading in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Aksigorta AS (AKGRT)  , the Turkish insurer in which Ageas
agreed to buy a 31 percent stake last month, rose the most in a
month after reaching a settlement with the Finance Ministry on
reducing back taxes. The company added 9 kurus, or 4.7 percent
to 2.01 liras. Aksigorta will pay 8.5 million liras ($5.4
million) in back taxes and the related fines were canceled,
Aksigorta said in a filing with the  Istanbul Stock Exchange 
today. The tax authorities had asked Aksigorta to pay a total
253.9 million liras, the company said on Jan. 10.    Asya Katilim Bankasi AS (ASYAB)  , an Islamic bank, gained
for a third day after the Haberturk newspaper reported that
Qatar Islamic Bank aims to buy a 25 percent stake. The shares
closed 2 kurus, or 0.7 percent, higher at 2.88 liras.  Borusan Mannesman Boru Sanayi & Ticaret AS (BRSAN TI), a
pipe manufacturer, gained 15 kurus, or 1 percent, to 15.40 liras
after Borusan Holding AS, its parent, said it is targeting sales
growth 15 percent to $4 billion this year while investing $325
million.    Celebi Hava Servisi AS (CLEBI)  , an airport services
company, surged 1.25 liras, or 5.4 percent, the biggest gain in
four months, to 24.60 liras after saying owner Celebi Havacilik
Holding AS decided to hold talks with foreign investors as it
considered “strategic alternatives.” The statement was made to
the exchange after markets closed yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Ankara 
